    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that there are different views, but that's a bit vague. if you had to pick a side for a country that is already struggling with high inflation and a massive deficit, wouldn't prioritizing the debt be the only responsible way to prevent a total collapse? or are you saying we should just keep spending regardless of the risk?",
