      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing debt reduction can help moderate inflation, but blanket cuts to social safety nets during an economic crisis often deepen poverty and stagnate growth. Most experts argue that in a struggling economy, the immediate focus should be stabilizing the deficit to restore confidence while strategically preserving safety net funding to maintain consumer demand. Ignoring the deficit entirely could lead to currency collapse, yet halting all spending would only worsen the human cost of inflation, making a nuanced balance the more responsible path forward.",
      "source": "target",
