      "content": "that \"nuance\" thing feels like a cop-out. if we know that high debt causes long-term instability and makes things way more expensive for everyone later, isn't it actually irresponsible to keep subsidizing social programs with borrowed money? isn't there a clear moral hierarchy where being fiscally sound has to come first to protect the future?",
